            <akn:heading>Oberservation of Daylight Saving Time Year-Round Upon Act by United States Congress</akn:heading>
            <akn:content>
              <akn:p>If the United States Congress amends 15 U.S.C. ยง 260a to authorize states to observe Daylight Saving Time year-round, the State of Alabama shall adopt Daylight Saving Time as the year-round standard of time for the entire state and all of its political subdivisions.</akn:p>
            </akn:content>
          </akn:section>
